  "texts": [
    "In the third line, we inserted the Fourier transform of the hopping element t(r) = 1 N AUC q t(q)e iq•r where A UC is the area of the graphene unit cell.",
    "In the fourth line, the sum over lattice sites is used to enforce q = p + G 1 G = p ′ + G ′2 G for some G G, G ′ G (in-plane Bragg scattering) belonging to the unrotated monolayer reciprocal lattice.",
    "At this stage, no additional approximations have been made.",
    "Now we exploit the fact that we are interested in momenta close to the monolayer Dirac points, so |p -K 1 |, |p ′ -K 2 | ≪ |K|.",
    "Since the the orbital overlap is smooth as a function of inter-orbital distance, the hopping element t(q) is expected to fall rapidly with |q|."
